rescue the effects that are observed that

1018
01:01:23.308 --> 01:01:23.428
we

1019
01:01:24.548 --> 01:01:28.408
facilitate upon Stat3 ablation in the nascent

1020
01:01:28.508 --> 01:01:32.048
tumors? And to accomplish this, we actually

1021
01:01:32.968 --> 01:01:36.708
overexpressed Chill in this inducible polyoma middle T model.

1022
01:01:37.248 --> 01:01:40.728
And what we found is that it indeed could

1023
01:01:40.848 --> 01:01:44.308
rescue all the tumorigenic and metastatic

1024
01:01:44.408 --> 01:01:47.748
effects observed in a Stat3 knockout, which

1025
01:01:47.768 --> 01:01:50.128
abrogates Chill expression in the tumor.

1026
01:01:51.588 --> 01:01:55.448
So this suggested that Chill was really the primary Stat3

1027
01:01:55.468 --> 01:01:58.768
target that's expressed by the tumor that's

1028
01:01:58.808 --> 01:02:00.188
responsible for this

1029
01:02:01.568 --> 01:02:04.388
effect on metastasis and primary tumor induction.

1030
01:02:05.208 --> 01:02:07.948
Another important observation that was made during this

1031
01:02:07.988 --> 01:02:11.828
study is that when we overexpress

1032
01:02:11.888 --> 01:02:15.708
Chill in the context of the mammary epithelium, we actually

1033
01:02:15.788 --> 01:02:19.308
facilitated metastasis on a large scale in the

1034
01:02:19.348 --> 01:02:21.528
wild-type middle T. In fact,

1035
01:02:22.488 --> 01:02:23.308
these tumors

1036
01:02:24.328 --> 01:02:27.848
basically populate the lung as early as six weeks

1037
01:02:28.508 --> 01:02:32.168
post-induction, so it's a very rapid induction of a metastatic

1038
01:02:32.248 --> 01:02:35.168
phenotype. And we were curious to further

1039
01:02:35.178 --> 01:02:38.478
understand how Chill was facilitating this

1040
01:02:38.508 --> 01:02:40.348
metastatic process.

1041
01:02:41.288 --> 01:02:45.088
We showed that, as we said it in the earlier paper, that

1042
01:02:45.468 --> 01:02:48.428
Chill is really responsible for recruiting neutrophils

1043
01:02:49.408 --> 01:02:51.928
to the mammary epithelium. So it's a major

1044
01:02:52.368 --> 01:02:55.888
chemoattractant for neutrophils, and it actually

1045
01:02:55.928 --> 01:02:59.788
induces netosis directly on that neutrophil population.

1046
01:03:00.228 --> 01:03:04.148
And all of those are exaggerated in the Chill overexpresser.

1047
01:03:05.508 --> 01:03:09.308
Now, one of the other aspects of breast cancer invasion

1048
01:03:09.888 --> 01:03:13.348
is a well-known process that occurs during tumor

1049
01:03:13.368 --> 01:03:17.128
genesis, particularly in this inducible middle T model and in

1050
01:03:17.248 --> 01:03:21.007
human breast cancer in general. That is that during

1051
01:03:21.088 --> 01:03:24.888
progression, you get initially formation of a ductal

1052
01:03:24.908 --> 01:03:28.568
carcinoma situ, which essentially is defined by

1053
01:03:28.608 --> 01:03:32.488
having tumor cells trapped in the lumen of the

1054
01:03:33.328 --> 01:03:36.508
duct. But they're still retained in that lumen by a

1055
01:03:37.228 --> 01:03:41.108
myoepithelial barrier that prevents invasion and

1056
01:03:41.208 --> 01:03:43.208
subsequent metastatic

1057
01:03:43.808 --> 01:03:46.768
colonization of the invasive ductal

1058
01:03:46.808 --> 01:03:50.738
carcinoma. Now, many studies have shown this

1059
01:03:50.788 --> 01:03:54.708
is really a key step in terms of the invasive potential

1060
01:03:55.028 --> 01:03:58.848
of breast cancer, and it's an important area to

1061
01:03:58.908 --> 01:04:02.688
quite understand this conversion from DCIS to invasive

1062
01:04:02.728 --> 01:04:06.388
breast cancer. One of the other interesting aspects that

1063
01:04:06.468 --> 01:04:10.128
coincided with our Chill studies is studies have shown

1064
01:04:10.208 --> 01:04:13.928
that this transition from DCIS to invasive breast

1065
01:04:14.008 --> 01:04:17.588
cancer is correlated with an increase in infiltrating

1066
01:04:17.668 --> 01:04:18.388
neutrophils.

1067
01:04:19.548 --> 01:04:23.528
So the next thing we wanted to assess is whether or not

1068
01:04:23.768 --> 01:04:27.388
the observed metastatic enhancement and metastatic

1069
01:04:27.488 --> 01:04:31.428
defect that we observed with the Chill knockout had anything to

1070
01:04:31.488 --> 01:04:34.108
do with the retention of the myoepithelial layer.

1071
01:04:34.768 --> 01:04:38.137
For those of you who are not familiar with myoepithelial markers,

1072
01:04:38.748 --> 01:04:39.968
CK14 is

1073
01:04:40.928 --> 01:04:44.718
essentially one of the hallmarks of the myoepithelial cell that

1074
01:04:44.828 --> 01:04:47.848
actually surrounds the adjacent luminal cell.

1075
01:04:48.648 --> 01:04:52.608
As you can see in the middle panel, the Chill knockout

1076
01:04:52.728 --> 01:04:56.068
tumors actually still retain an intact

1077
01:04:56.108 --> 01:04:59.888
myoepithelial layer, as evidenced by the uniform circular

1078
01:05:00.048 --> 01:05:03.608
staining of CK14 around that

1079
01:05:03.668 --> 01:05:07.448
emerging tumor. And just to remind you, these are the

1080
01:05:07.708 --> 01:05:11.448
same Chill-deficient tumors that are incapable of metastatic

1081
01:05:11.488 --> 01:05:14.888
progression. By contrast, if we look at the Chill

1082
01:05:14.948 --> 01:05:18.588
overexpresser, that myoepithelial layer is completely

1083
01:05:18.628 --> 01:05:22.008
gone, and this is at a similar time point of induction,

1084
01:05:22.608 --> 01:05:25.628
implying that Chill is really an important

1085
01:05:26.668 --> 01:05:30.308
parameter in allowing retention of that myoepithelial cells.

1086
01:05:30.908 --> 01:05:34.008
Now, as I mentioned in my introduction, that Chill is a major

1087
01:05:34.148 --> 01:05:38.048
neutrophil attractant. The next question we want to address,

1088
01:05:38.548 --> 01:05:42.428
are neutrophils important in the retention of this myoepithelial layer?

1089
01:05:43.468 --> 01:05:47.388
So we actually did a further analysis

1090
01:05:47.428 --> 01:05:50.888
of another transgenic strain, in this case, a C3

1091
01:05:50.988 --> 01:05:51.428
tag

1092
01:05:52.908 --> 01:05:56.548
model, which models basal breast cancer, and we could

1093
01:05:56.628 --> 01:06:00.148
show, like the polyoma middle T tag tumor,

1094
01:06:00.638 --> 01:06:04.288
that the C3 tag knockout of Chill resulted in

1095
01:06:04.548 --> 01:06:08.527
similar retention of CK14 myoepithelial cells.

1096
01:06:08.588 --> 01:06:11.958
So in an independent breast cancer subtype, we could

1097
01:06:12.308 --> 01:06:16.298
actually show that Chill is really an important parameter in

1098
01:06:16.768 --> 01:06:20.048
losing this myoepithelial layer, which again

1099
01:06:20.188 --> 01:06:23.168
correlates with the invasive potential of that tumor.

1100
01:06:24.828 --> 01:06:28.368
Now, whether neutrophils were involved in this process, given that

1101
01:06:28.748 --> 01:06:32.008
Chill is an important neutrophil chemoattractant, was next

1102
01:06:32.048 --> 01:06:34.948
assessed by doing a neutrophil depletion.

1103
01:06:34.988 --> 01:06:38.568
And we accomplished this by basically using a

1104
01:06:38.688 --> 01:06:40.808
depletion antibody for neutrophils,

1105
01:06:41.768 --> 01:06:45.548
namely anti-Ly6G. And we actually did

1106
01:06:45.628 --> 01:06:49.088
this in the middle T model. We found that

1107
01:06:49.148 --> 01:06:52.848
neutrophil depletion essentially prevented the

1108
01:06:52.888 --> 01:06:56.828
myoepithelial dissolution, as you can see from retention of

1109
01:06:56.888 --> 01:06:59.588
CK14 and Smoc

1110
01:07:00.028 --> 01:07:03.928
anti-Smoc as markers of the myoepithelial

1111
01:07:04.468 --> 01:07:07.928
layer. We further confirmed that by using independent

1112
01:07:08.028 --> 01:07:11.938
markers of myoepithelial cells, calponin 1 and p63.

1113
01:07:12.608 --> 01:07:16.188
And again, we could show that neutrophil depletion actually

1114
01:07:16.208 --> 01:07:18.828
prevented this dissolution of the myoepithelial

1115
01:07:19.008 --> 01:07:22.816
barrier.So what

1116
01:07:22.896 --> 01:07:26.576
processes of neutrophils are important in the loss of the

1117
01:07:28.776 --> 01:07:32.136
myepithelial layer? As we talked about earlier,

1118
01:07:32.256 --> 01:07:35.036
netosis is one of the processes by which

1119
01:07:35.876 --> 01:07:38.976
neutrophils can be induced to actually create

1120
01:07:39.156 --> 01:07:41.996
immune suppressive microenvironment.

1121
01:07:42.636 --> 01:07:45.916
Another potential explanation for this observation

1122
01:07:46.476 --> 01:07:50.116
is that neutrophil could degranulate at the site of the

1123
01:07:52.776 --> 01:07:56.716
emerging tumor, and thereby modulate the extracellular

1124
01:07:56.816 --> 01:08:00.796
matrix environment within that tumor and actually have a

1125
01:08:00.856 --> 01:08:02.636
major effect on myepithelial

1126
01:08:03.696 --> 01:08:04.436
retention.

1127
01:08:05.316 --> 01:08:06.876
Now, these particular

1128
01:08:08.776 --> 01:08:12.476
processes of degranulation can be actually chemically

1129
01:08:12.536 --> 01:08:16.476
inhibited by a particular inhibitor called Nex-20, which

1130
01:08:16.516 --> 01:08:19.096
prevents neutrophil degranulation.

1131
01:08:20.036 --> 01:08:23.956
Again, when we treated the Middle T tumors that emerged into

1132
01:08:24.016 --> 01:08:27.916
these mice with Nex-20, we found that they retained the

1133
01:08:27.956 --> 01:08:29.096
CK14

1134
01:08:30.456 --> 01:08:34.416
myepithelial layer, indicating that degranulation was

1135
01:08:34.536 --> 01:08:38.096
really a key event in allowing dissolution of this

1136
01:08:38.137 --> 01:08:41.976
myepithelial layer. And we could further validate

1137
01:08:42.036 --> 01:08:46.016
that by using other markers of myepithelium, including

1138
01:08:46.076 --> 01:08:49.396
calponin 1 and p63. And again,

1139
01:08:51.036 --> 01:08:54.616
treatment of Nex-20 actually prevented this

1140
01:08:54.637 --> 01:08:56.856
dissolution of the myepithelial barrier.

1141
01:08:58.056 --> 01:08:59.516
So this raises a question,

1142
01:09:00.337 --> 01:09:03.137
which component of the granules are actually

1143
01:09:03.217 --> 01:09:06.576
responsible for this observed

1144
01:09:08.916 --> 01:09:12.496
loss of the myepithelium? So one of the important

1145
01:09:12.976 --> 01:09:16.276
clues to this came from the fact that neutrophil

1146
01:09:16.337 --> 01:09:18.316
elastase is really an important

1147
01:09:19.736 --> 01:09:23.677
enzyme secreted by neutrophils that actually is important

1148
01:09:23.717 --> 01:09:26.757
in degradation and remodeling of the matrix.

1149
01:09:27.436 --> 01:09:31.297
Further to this, a previous study by the Kia Marski lab

1150
01:09:31.717 --> 01:09:35.566
had shown that the same model, the polyoma Middle T model, when made it

1151
01:09:35.616 --> 01:09:39.056
to the neutrophil elastase knockout, actually blocked

1152
01:09:39.096 --> 01:09:42.186
metastatic progression, implying that this

1153
01:09:42.257 --> 01:09:46.217
particular component was perhaps one of the major

1154
01:09:46.236 --> 01:09:49.316
neutrophil components of degranulation that was

1155
01:09:49.376 --> 01:09:53.196
responsible for this process. As it turns out,

1156
01:09:53.236 --> 01:09:55.656
there's a specific small molecule

1157
01:09:55.696 --> 01:09:59.636
inhibitor, Alvestat, that basically is a

1158
01:09:59.656 --> 01:10:02.916
reversible inhibitor of neutrophil elastase.

1159
01:10:03.436 --> 01:10:07.256
So we next asked the question whether targeting neutrophil elastase

1160
01:10:07.776 --> 01:10:11.616
could have an impact on retention of the myepithelial

1161
01:10:11.756 --> 01:10:12.086
layer.

1162
01:10:13.176 --> 01:10:16.716
As you might anticipate, firstly, we showed that

1163
01:10:16.776 --> 01:10:20.616
Alvestat does successfully inhibit neutrophil elastase upon

1164
01:10:20.736 --> 01:10:24.376
treatment in this model by looking at a number of known neutrophil

1165
01:10:25.156 --> 01:10:28.916
elastase substrates, namely TSP-1 and

1166
01:10:29.036 --> 01:10:32.916
elastin. As anticipated, the Alvestat-treated

1167
01:10:32.996 --> 01:10:33.376
mice

1168
01:10:34.256 --> 01:10:38.156
basically showed inhibition of cleavage of these

1169
01:10:38.236 --> 01:10:38.516
key

1170
01:10:39.456 --> 01:10:42.516
neutrophil elastase products. So the

1171
01:10:43.056 --> 01:10:46.436
particular Alvestat is acting as an

1172
01:10:46.516 --> 01:10:49.496
on-target inhibitor of neutrophil elastase.

1173
01:10:51.356 --> 01:10:53.825
So we next asked whether using

1174
01:10:54.776 --> 01:10:58.686
Alvestat could we actually prevent this myepithelial dissolution.

1175
01:10:59.296 --> 01:11:03.096
Again, using the inducible polyoma Middle T, we showed

1176
01:11:03.216 --> 01:11:06.836
that treatment of these inducible Middle T with

1177
01:11:06.876 --> 01:11:10.856
Alvestat essentially resulted in dissolution of that

1178
01:11:10.896 --> 01:11:14.876
myepithelial layer. So you had retention of CK14,

1179
01:11:15.596 --> 01:11:19.076
calponin 1, and p63 in these Alvestat-treated

1180
01:11:19.276 --> 01:11:22.836
animals. We further showed that these

1181
01:11:22.936 --> 01:11:26.636
Alvestat-treated animals actually showed

1182
01:11:26.896 --> 01:11:30.746
a reduction in circulating tumor cells, indicating

1183
01:11:30.796 --> 01:11:33.596
that they were essentially preventing

1184
01:11:33.936 --> 01:11:36.456
extravasation of those tumor

1185
01:11:38.156 --> 01:11:41.816
cells into bloodstream, presumably through retention of that

1186
01:11:41.836 --> 01:11:45.776
myepithelial boundary. So the next question to

1187
01:11:45.836 --> 01:11:48.796
address is: How is neutrophil elastase

1188
01:11:49.276 --> 01:11:52.376
compromising that myepithelial layer?

1189
01:11:53.416 --> 01:11:56.436
Now, as I mentioned, neutrophil elastase is an important

1190
01:11:57.516 --> 01:12:00.836
modulator of the extracellular matrix through

1191
01:12:00.876 --> 01:12:04.316
degradation of key matrix components such as laminin and

1192
01:12:04.376 --> 01:12:07.856
collagens. And they are actually supporting basement

1193
01:12:07.956 --> 01:12:11.096
matrix components that allow the

1194
01:12:11.136 --> 01:12:14.736
myepithelial cell to survive through its integrin receptors.

1195
01:12:15.376 --> 01:12:19.166
So you can well imagine that upon degradation of laminin and

1196
01:12:19.336 --> 01:12:23.126
collagens, you lose that supporting basement membrane,

1197
01:12:24.016 --> 01:12:27.096
and as a consequence of that, integrins become

1198
01:12:27.116 --> 01:12:30.716
disengaged, and those myepithelial cells undergo a

1199
01:12:30.736 --> 01:12:34.636
process of anoikis or programmed cell death due to lack

1200
01:12:34.656 --> 01:12:36.156
adhesion to matrix.

1201
01:12:38.096 --> 01:12:41.676
So firstly, we wanted to see whether or not Chill promotes

1202
01:12:41.756 --> 01:12:45.716
metastasis through neutrophil-mediated ECM

1203
01:12:45.776 --> 01:12:49.696
modeling. And again, if we look at our system

1204
01:12:49.736 --> 01:12:53.576
where we overexpress Chill in the Middle T system, we could show

1205
01:12:53.676 --> 01:12:57.216
that Chill, through its recruitment of neutrophils, can

1206
01:12:57.296 --> 01:13:00.476
massively remodel the laminin and collagen

1207
01:13:00.836 --> 01:13:04.556
extracellular matrix, essentially degrading it such that

1208
01:13:04.616 --> 01:13:07.836
it essentially is eliminated. And as a

1209
01:13:08.616 --> 01:13:10.796
result of that,

1210
01:13:11.776 --> 01:13:13.796
you can actually see that

1211
01:13:15.736 --> 01:13:19.156
essentially you lose that supporting basement membrane that the

1212
01:13:19.196 --> 01:13:20.296
myepithelial cell

1213
01:13:21.176 --> 01:13:25.152
requires.We further showed that as a consequence of this,

1214
01:13:25.772 --> 01:13:29.362
if you delete or deplete neutrophils in these CHILL

1215
01:13:29.432 --> 01:13:32.632
overexpressing mice, you could abrogate that phenomena.

1216
01:13:32.692 --> 01:13:35.732
So again, this CHILL-dependent remodeling of the

1217
01:13:35.772 --> 01:13:38.572
ECM was dependent on neutrophils.

1218
01:13:39.092 --> 01:13:42.512
And again, as I further alluded to, the numbers of circulating

1219
01:13:42.652 --> 01:13:45.212
polyamidal T tumor cells were

1220
01:13:45.572 --> 01:13:49.512
correspondingly reduced when we actually looked at

1221
01:13:49.572 --> 01:13:52.472
this Lys6G depletion of neutrophils.

1222
01:13:52.972 --> 01:13:56.912
And again, if you look at the retention of laminin

1223
01:13:56.952 --> 01:14:00.772
and collagen IV, you can see that loss of neutrophils in this

1224
01:14:01.092 --> 01:14:05.052
overexpression scenario led to retention of those

1225
01:14:05.292 --> 01:14:09.212
basement membrane components, indicating that this

1226
01:14:09.272 --> 01:14:13.092
really is a CHILL-dependent neutrophil remodeling of the

1227
01:14:13.132 --> 01:14:16.952
ECM that's required for retention of the

1228
01:14:16.992 --> 01:14:20.352
myepithelial cells and essentially

1229
01:14:20.632 --> 01:14:24.072
survival of those. To further address this,

1230
01:14:24.572 --> 01:14:27.592
we showed that using an alvestat, we could

1231
01:14:27.752 --> 01:14:31.732
prevent this degradation of laminin and collagen,

1232
01:14:31.812 --> 01:14:35.652
again implicating the importance of neutrophil elastase

1233
01:14:36.072 --> 01:14:39.392
in remodeling these key components of the basement membrane.

1234
01:14:40.932 --> 01:14:44.452
Now, as I mentioned previously, that this basement

1235
01:14:44.832 --> 01:14:48.472
membrane serves as an important cell survival

1236
01:14:48.612 --> 01:14:51.012
aspect for myepithelial cell growth

1237
01:14:51.912 --> 01:14:55.772
and retention. And we can see from-- Sorry, I'll go

1238
01:14:55.872 --> 01:14:59.152
back. You can see that when we look at the

1239
01:15:00.492 --> 01:15:01.732
active apoptotic

1240
01:15:02.812 --> 01:15:05.872
cell death within the CK14 population,

1241
01:15:06.692 --> 01:15:10.672
when we use alvestat, we essentially block this myepithelial cell

1242
01:15:10.772 --> 01:15:14.232
death. And this, again, is correlated with,

1243
01:15:14.632 --> 01:15:18.372
again, engagement of integrins on the myepithelial cells with

1244
01:15:18.792 --> 01:15:21.592
key integrin pathways such as focal fact,

1245
01:15:22.072 --> 01:15:25.172
implying that neutrophils

1246
01:15:25.312 --> 01:15:28.732
really essentially destroy this supporting basement

1247
01:15:28.772 --> 01:15:32.022
membrane that supports myepithelial retention.

1248
01:15:32.572 --> 01:15:36.412
And that, in turn, prevents metastatic spread of

1249
01:15:36.472 --> 01:15:38.652
the invasive breast cancer.

1250
01:15:40.032 --> 01:15:43.972
So what I've basically shown you today is neutrophils through the

1251
01:15:44.052 --> 01:15:47.892
CHILL axis really are important in remodeling

1252
01:15:47.932 --> 01:15:51.242
the ECM as a driver of cancer progression and

1253
01:15:51.312 --> 01:15:55.252
metastasis. And they do so via a number of different

1254
01:15:55.312 --> 01:15:59.041
mechanisms. First, through degranulation and neutrophil elastase,

1255
01:15:59.492 --> 01:16:02.852
which turns over the basement membrane and causes the

1256
01:16:02.872 --> 01:16:06.792
myepithelial cells to lose essentially important

1257
01:16:06.832 --> 01:16:10.612
cell survival signal. This then allows the emerging

1258
01:16:10.752 --> 01:16:12.972
tumor cell to contact the

1259
01:16:14.552 --> 01:16:15.112
surrounding

1260
01:16:16.432 --> 01:16:19.572
stroma and begin its invasion process.

1261
01:16:20.932 --> 01:16:24.652
The second mechanism, as I alluded to at the beginning of my talk, is the

1262
01:16:24.712 --> 01:16:26.412
capacity of

1263
01:16:27.452 --> 01:16:31.422
neutrophils to undergo netosis and essentially form nets around

1264
01:16:31.422 --> 01:16:35.412
those tumors, thereby preventing infiltrating T cells

1265
01:16:35.492 --> 01:16:39.482
from essentially eliminating those nascent

1266
01:16:39.512 --> 01:16:43.392
tumor cells. So CHILL actually activates both those

1267
01:16:43.512 --> 01:16:46.892
axes, and both probably are involved in allowing

1268
01:16:46.972 --> 01:16:50.732
those tumors to eventually escape and

1269
01:16:51.632 --> 01:16:54.792
eventually colonize distal metastatic sites.

1270
01:16:55.832 --> 01:16:56.892
So in conclusion,

1271
01:16:57.952 --> 01:17:01.832
there really is important data that I presented

1272
01:17:01.852 --> 01:17:05.332
here that shows that CHILL is a major driver of metastasis

1273
01:17:05.892 --> 01:17:09.292
